n Berlin this summer.\u003C/p>",{"headings":31,"localImagePaths":43,"remoteImagePaths":44,"frontmatter":45,"imagePaths":48},[32,36,40],{"depth":33,"slug":34,"text":35},2,"the-process","The Process",{"depth":37,"slug":38,"text":39},3,"track-selection-criteria","Track Selection Criteria",{"depth":33,"slug":41,"text":42},"key-tracks","Key Tracks",[],[],{"title":14,"description":15,"pubDate":46,"category":17,"tags":47,"readTime":22,"lang":23,"translationKey":24},["Date","2024-12-28T00:00:00.000Z"],[19,20,21],[],"en/best-songs-2024-dj-mix.md","en/typography-in-vr",{"id":50,"data":52,"body":63,"filePath":64,"digest":65,"rendered":66,"legacyId":76},{"title":53,"description":54,"pubDate":55,"category":56,"tags":57,"readTime":61,"lang":23,"translationKey":62},"Typography in VR","How do we read when the screen surrounds us? Exploring readability and contrast in 3D interfaces.",["Date","2024-07-05T00:00:00.000Z"],"Design",[58,59,60],"VR","Typography","Spatial Computing","7 min","typography-in-vr","Spatial computing presents new challenges for text rendering. We analyze standard practices for font sizing and placement in a 360-degree environment.","src/content/blog/en/typography-in-vr.md","ba36930c77019e76",{"html":67,"metadata":68},"\u003Cp>Spatial computing presents new challenges for text rendering. We analyze standard practices for font sizing and placement in a 360-degree environment.\u003C/p>",{"headings":69,"localImagePaths":70,"remoteImagePaths":71,"frontmatter":72,"imagePaths":75},[],[],[],{"title":53,"description":54,"pubDate":73,"category":56,"tags":74,"readTime":61,"lang":23,"translationKey":62},["Date","2024-07-05T00:00:00.000Z"],[58,59,60],[],"en/typography-in-vr.md","en/the-139-mix-tape",{"id":77,"data":79,"body":89,"filePath":90,"digest":91,"rendered":92,"legacyId":102},{"title":80,"description":81,"pubDate":82,"category":17,"tags":83,"readTime":87,"lang":23,"translationKey":88},"The 139 Mix Tape","What do you get when take the best parts of 139 songs, slice them up, and paste them back together? 45 minutes of awesome beats.",["Date","2024-09-10T00:00:00.000Z"],[84,85,86],"Mashup","WebAudio","Sampling","45 min","139-mix-tape","A technical breakdown of how this was achieved using **WebAudio API** to stitch together samples dynamically in the browser.","src/content/blog/en/the-139-mix-tape.md","85f71f607d62accd",{"html":93,"metadata":94},"\u003Cp>A technical breakdown of how this was achieved using \u003Cstrong>WebAudio API\u003C/strong> to stitch together samples dynamically in the browser.\u003C/p>",{"headings":95,"localImagePaths":96,"remoteImagePaths":97,"frontmatter":98,"imagePaths":101},[],[],[],{"title":80,"description":81,"pubDate":99,"category":17,"tags":100,"readTime":87,"lang":23,"translationKey":88},["Date","2024-09-10T00:00:00.000Z"],[84,85,86],[],"en/the-139-mix-tape.md","en/immutable-infrastructures",{"id":103,"data":105,"body":116,"filePath":117,"digest":118,"rendered":119,"legacyId":129},{"title":106,"description":107,"pubDate":108,"category":109,"tags":110,"readTime":114,"lang":23,"translationKey":115},"Immutable Infrastructures","Why we should stop treating servers like pets and start treating them like cattle. A deep dive into modern DevOps practices.",["Date","2024-08-22T00:00:00.000Z"],"Code",[111,112,113],"DevOps","Infrastructure","Docker","12 min","immutable-infrastructures","The shift to **containerization** and **orchestration** has fundamentally changed how we deploy software.","src/content/blog/en/immutable-infrastructures.md","38deb58c659fcf20",{"html":120,"metadata":121},"\u003Cp>The shift to \u003Cstrong>containerization\u003C/strong> and \u003Cstrong>orchestration\u003C/strong> has fundamentally changed how we deploy software.\u003C/p>",{"headings":122,"localImagePaths":123,"remoteImagePaths":124,"frontmatter":125,"imagePaths":128},[],[],[],{"title":106,"description":107,"pubDate":126,"category":109,"tags":127,"readTime":114,"lang":23,"translationKey":115},["Date","2024-08-22T00:00:00.000Z"],[111,112,113],[],"en/immutable-infrastructures.md","zh/best-songs-2024-dj-mix",{"id":130,"data":132,"body":139,"filePath":140,"digest":141,"rendered":142,"legacyId":158},{"title":133,"description":134,"pubDate":135,"category":17,"tags":136,"readTime":137,"lang":138,"translationKey":24},"2024 年度最佳歌曲 – DJ 混音","这是迄今为止最难制作的年终混音之一，仅仅是因为 2024 年有太多好听的曲目可供选择。",["Date","2024-12-28T00:00:00.000Z"],[19,20,21],"10 分钟","zh","这是迄今为止最难制作的年终混音之一，仅仅是因为 2024 年有太多好听的曲目可供选择。将它们全部塞进一小时是不可能的任务。不过 58 首曲目还是做到了，今年延续了现代舞池中巨大的节奏多样性，从慢速迪斯科到快节奏的 Techno。\n\n## 制作过程\n\n我首先整理了一份今年我喜欢的超过 **500 首曲目** 的清单。从那里开始，就是一个将其削减到绝对精华的过程。重点在于流畅度和能量，确保混音从头到尾都在讲述一个故事。\n\n> “音乐是音符之间的沉默。” — *克劳德·德彪西*\n\n### 选曲标准\n\n我是如何对这些曲目进行排名的：\n\n1. **氛围**：它让你想动起来吗？\n2. **制作质量**：混音干净吗？\n3. **原创性**：这个低音线我以前听过 100 遍了吗？\n\n| 排名 | 艺术家 | 曲目 | 流派 |\n|------|--------|-------|-------|\n| 1 | Fred Again.. | Places to Be | Electronic |\n| 2 | Peggy Gou | 1+1=11 | House |\n| 3 | Overmono | Blow Out | Techno |\n\n## 关键曲目\n\n杰出的曲目包括 **Fred Again..** 的新发行，**Purple Disco Machine** 的迪斯科复兴热单，以及一些定义了今年夏天柏林俱乐部场景的地下佳作。","src/content/blog/zh/best-songs-2024-dj-mix.md","720c2b585a196cca",{"html":143,"metadata":144},"\u003Cp>这是迄今为止最难制作的年终混音之一，仅仅是因为 2024 年有太多好听的曲目可供选择。将它们全部塞进一小时是不可能的任务。不过 58 首曲目还是做到了，今年延续了现代舞池中巨大的节奏多样性，从慢速迪斯科到快节奏的 Techno。\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"制作过程\">制作过程\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>我首先整理了一份今年我喜欢的超过 \u003Cstrong>500 首曲目\u003C/strong> 的清单。从那里开始，就是一个将其削减到绝对精华的过程。重点在于流畅度和能量，确保混音从头到尾都在讲述一个故事。\u003C/p>\n\u003Cblockquote>\n\u003Cp>“音乐是音符之间的沉默。” — \u003Cem>克劳德·德彪西\u003C/em>\u003C/p>\n\u003C/blockquote>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"选曲标准\">选曲标准\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>我是如何对这些曲目进行排名的：\u003C/p>\n\u003Col>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>氛围\u003C/strong>：它让你想动起来吗？\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>制作质量\u003C/strong>：混音干净吗？\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>原创性\u003C/strong>：这个低音线我以前听过 100 遍了吗？\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ol>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003Ctable>\u003Cthead>\u003Ctr>\u003Cth>排名\u003C/th>\u003Cth>艺术家\u003C/th>\u003Cth>曲目\u003C/th>\u003Cth>流派\u003C/th>\u003C/tr>\u003C/thead>\u003Ctbody>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>1\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Fred Again..\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Places to Be\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Electronic\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>2\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Peggy Gou\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>1+1=11\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>House\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003Ctr>\u003Ctd>3\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Overmono\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Blow Out\u003C/td>\u003Ctd>Techno\u003C/td>\u003C/tr>\u003C/tbody>\u003C/table>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"关键曲目\">关键曲目\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>杰出的曲目包括 \u003Cstrong>Fred Again..\u003C/strong> 的新发行，\u003Cstrong>Purple Disco Machine\u003C/strong> 的迪斯科复兴热单，以及一些定义了今年夏天柏林俱乐部场景的地下佳作。\u003C/p>",{"headings":145,"localImagePaths":152,"remoteImagePaths":153,"frontmatter":154,"imagePaths":157},[146,148,150],{"depth":33,"slug":147,"text":147},"制作过程",{"depth":37,"slug":149,"text":149},"选曲标准",{"depth":33,"slug":151,"text":151},"关键曲目",[],[],{"title":133,"description":134,"pubDate":155,"category":17,"tags":156,"readTime":137,"lang":138,"translationKey":24},["Date","2024-12-28T00:00:00.000Z"],[19,20,21],[],"zh/best-songs-2024-dj-mix.md","zh/immutable-infrastructures",{"id":159,"data":161,"body":167,"filePath":168,"digest":169,"rendered":170,"legacyId":180},{"title":162,"description":163,"pubDate":164,"category":109,"tags":165,"readTime":166,"lang":138,"translationKey":115},"不可变基础设施","为什么我们应该停止像对待宠物一样对待服务器，而开始像对待牲畜一样对待它们。深入探讨现代 DevOps 实践。",["Date","2024-08-22T00:00:00.000Z"],[111,112,113],"12 分钟","向 **容器化** 和 **编排** 的转变从根本上改变了我们要部署软件的方式。","src/content/blog/zh/immutable-infrastructures.md","8250b36f707b7c3d",{"html":171,"metadata":172},"\u003Cp>向 \u003Cstrong>容器化\u003C/strong> 和 \u003Cstrong>编排\u003C/strong> 的转变从根本上改变了我们要部署软件的方式。\u003C/p>",{"headings":173,"localImagePaths":174,"remoteImagePaths":175,"frontmatter":176,"imagePaths":179},[],[],[],{"title":162,"description":163,"pubDate":177,"category":109,"tags":178,"readTime":166,"lang":138,"translationKey":115},["Date","2024-08-22T00:00:00.000Z"],[111,112,113],[],"zh/immutable-infrastructures.md","en/resolution-dependent-layout",{"id":181,"data":183,"body":194,"filePath":195,"digest":196,"rendered":197,"legacyId":213},{"title":184,"description":185,"pubDate":186,"category":187,"tags":188,"readTime":192,"lang":23,"translationKey":193},"Resolution Dependent Layout","Way before there was a thing called responsive design, I wrote about a technique that could enable a website to change its design based on the size of the screen.",["Date","2024-10-02T00:00:00.000Z"],"CSS",[189,190,191],"Responsive Design","History","Layout","8 min","resolution-dependent-layout","Before media queries became a standard, we had to use JavaScript hacks to detect viewport width. This article looks back at the history of responsive design and how far we have come.\n\n## The Old Way\n\nIn 2004, we did things differently.\n\n> \"The web is fluid, but our designs are rigid.\"\n\nWe used `window.onresize` events to swap stylesheets. It was clumsy, slow, and prone to breaking.\n\n## The New Way\n\nToday, we have **CSS Container Queries** which allow us to style elements based on their parent container size, not just the viewport.\n\n```css\n@container (min-width: 700px) {\n  .card {\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;\n  }\n}\n```","src/content/blog/en/resolution-dependent-layout.md","e70878cdc4503885",{"html":198,"metadata":199},"\u003Cp>Before media queries became a standard, we had to use JavaScript hacks to detect viewport width. This article looks back at the history of responsive design and how far we have come.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"the-old-way\">The Old Way\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>In 2004, we did things differently.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cblockquote>\n\u003Cp>“The web is fluid, but our designs are rigid.”\u003C/p>\n\u003C/blockquote>\n\u003Cp>We used \u003Ccode>window.onresize\u003C/code> events to swap stylesheets. It was clumsy, slow, and prone to breaking.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"the-new-way\">The New Way\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Today, we have \u003Cstrong>CSS Container Queries\u003C/strong> which allow us to style elements based on their parent container size, not just the viewport.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cpre class=\"astro-code github-dark\" style=\"background-color:#24292e;color:#e1e4e8; overflow-x: auto;\" tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"css\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">@container\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\"> (min-width: 700px) {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#B392F0\">  .card\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#79B8FF\">    display\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">: \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#79B8FF\">grid\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">;\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#79B8FF\">    grid-template-columns\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">: \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#79B8FF\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">fr\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#79B8FF\"> 1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">fr\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">;\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">  }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">}\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>",{"headings":200,"localImagePaths":207,"remoteImagePaths":208,"frontmatter":209,"imagePaths":212},[201,204],{"depth":33,"slug":202,"text":203},"the-old-way","The Old Way",{"depth":33,"slug":205,"text":206},"the-new-way","The New Way",[],[],{"title":184,"description":185,"pubDate":210,"category":187,"tags":211,"readTime":192,"lang":23,"translationKey":193},["Date","2024-10-02T00:00:00.000Z"],[189,190,191],[],"en/resolution-dependent-layout.md","zh/resolution-dependent-layout",{"id":214,"data":216,"body":222,"filePath":223,"digest":224,"rendered":225,"legacyId":239},{"title":217,"description":218,"pubDate":219,"category":187,"tags":220,"readTime":221,"lang":138,"translationKey":193},"分辨率依赖布局","早在响应式设计出现之前，我就写过一种能够使网站根据屏幕大小改变其设计的技术。",["Date","2024-10-02T00:00:00.000Z"],[189,190,191],"8 分钟","在媒体查询成为标准之前，我们不得不使用 JavaScript 来检测视口宽度。本文回顾了响应式设计的历史以及我们取得的进步。\n\n## 旧方法\n\n在 2004 年，我们做事的方式截然不同。\n\n> “网络是流动的，但我们的设计是僵化的。”\n\n我们使用 `window.onresize` 事件来交换样式表。这很笨拙、缓慢，而且容易出错。\n\n## 新方法\n\n今天，我们有了 **CSS 容器查询**，它允许我们根据父容器的大小而不仅仅是视口来设置元素的样式。\n\n```css\n@container (min-width: 700px) {\n  .card {\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;\n  }\n}\n```","src/content/blog/zh/resolution-dependent-layout.md","73034267d5cae366",{"html":226,"metadata":227},"\u003Cp>在媒体查询成为标准之前，我们不得不使用 JavaScript 来检测视口宽度。本文回顾了响应式设计的历史以及我们取得的进步。\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"旧方法\">旧方法\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>在 2004 年，我们做事的方式截然不同。\u003C/p>\n\u003Cblockquote>\n\u003Cp>“网络是流动的，但我们的设计是僵化的。”\u003C/p>\n\u003C/blockquote>\n\u003Cp>我们使用 \u003Ccode>window.onresize\u003C/code> 事件来交换样式表。这很笨拙、缓慢，而且容易出错。\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"新方法\">新方法\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>今天，我们有了 \u003Cstrong>CSS 容器查询\u003C/strong>，它允许我们根据父容器的大小而不仅仅是视口来设置元素的样式。\u003C/p>\n\u003Cpre class=\"astro-code github-dark\" style=\"background-color:#24292e;color:#e1e4e8; overflow-x: auto;\" tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"css\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">@container\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\"> (min-width: 700px) {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#B392F0\">  .card\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#79B8FF\">    display\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">: \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#79B8FF\">grid\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">;\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#79B8FF\">    grid-template-columns\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">: \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#79B8FF\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">fr\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#79B8FF\"> 1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">fr\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">;\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">  }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">}\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>",{"headings":228,"localImagePaths":233,"remoteImagePaths":234,"frontmatter":235,"imagePaths":238},[229,231],{"depth":33,"slug":230,"text":230},"旧方法",{"depth":33,"slug":232,"text":232},"新方法",[],[],{"title":217,"description":218,"pubDate":236,"category":187,"tags":237,"readTime":221,"lang":138,"translationKey":193},["Date","2024-10-02T00:00:00.000Z"],[189,190,191],[],"zh/resolution-dependent-layout.md","zh/typography-in-vr",{"id":240,"data":242,"body":248,"filePath":249,"digest":250,"rendered":251,"legacyId":261},{"title":243,"description":244,"pubDate":245,"category":56,"tags":246,"readTime":247,"lang":138,"translationKey":62},"VR 中的排版","当屏幕包围我们时，我们如何阅读？探索 3D 界面中的可读性和对比度。",["Date","2024-07-05T00:00:00.000Z"],[58,59,60],"7 分钟","空间计算给文本渲染带来了新的挑战。我们分析了 360 度环境中字体大小和放置的标准做法。","src/content/blog/zh/typography-in-vr.md","ebca18ca39a8abc3",{"html":252,"metadata":253},"\u003Cp>空间计算给文本渲染带来了新的挑战。我们分析了 360 度环境中字体大小和放置的标准做法。\u003C/p>",{"headings":254,"localImagePaths":255,"remoteImagePaths":256,"frontmatter":257,"imagePaths":260},[],[],[],{"title":243,"description":244,"pubDate":258,"category":56,"tags":259,"readTime":247,"lang":138,"translationKey":62},["Date","2024-07-05T00:00:00.000Z"],[58,59,60],[],"zh/typography-in-vr.md","zh/the-139-mix-tape",{"id":262,"data":264,"body":270,"filePath":271,"digest":272,"rendered":273,"legacyId":283},{"title":265,"description":266,"pubDate":267,"category":17,"tags":268,"readTime":269,"lang":138,"translationKey":88},"139 混音带","当你取下 139 首歌的最精彩部分，将它们切碎并重新拼凑在一起时会得到什么？45 分钟的精彩节拍。",["Date","2024-09-10T00:00:00.000Z"],[84,85,86],"45 分钟","关于如何使用 **WebAudio API** 在浏览器中动态拼接样本的技术分解。","src/content/blog/zh/the-139-mix-tape.md","834b2ffef1555389",{"html":274,"metadata":275},"\u003Cp>关于如何使用 \u003Cstrong>WebAudio API\u003C/strong> 在浏览器中动态拼接样本的技术分解。\u003C/p>",{"headings":276,"localImagePaths":277,"remoteImagePaths":278,"frontmatter":279,"imagePaths":282},[],[],[],{"title":265,"description":266,"pubDate":280,"category":17,"tags":281,"readTime":269,"lang":138,"translationKey":88},["Date","2024-09-10T00:00:00.000Z"],[84,85,86],[],"zh/the-139-mix-tape.md","en/code-and-typography",{"id":284,"data":286,"body":294,"filePath":295,"digest":296,"rendered":297,"legacyId":316},{"title":287,"description":288,"pubDate":289,"category":187,"tags":290,"readTime":292,"lang":23,"translationKey":293},"Code & Typography","A showcase of how we handle code blocks and typography in this new system using Markdown.",["Date","2024-11-15T00:00:00.000Z"],[291,109,56],"Markdown","5 min","code-typography","We consume content at a staggering rate. But are we actually reading? Or are we just scanning? In this essay, I explore the impact of typography on reading comprehension.\n\n## Typography Principles\n\nWhen designing for the web, we must consider:\n\n- **Hierarchy**: Using size and weight to guide the eye.\n- **Contrast**: Ensuring text is legible against the background.\n- **Spacing**: Giving elements room to breathe.\n\n### Code Example\n\nHere is a snippet of **TypeScript** code that demonstrates how we handle the layout:\n\n```typescript\ninterface LayoutProps {\n  children: React.ReactNode;\n  isMobile: boolean;\n}\n\nconst Layout: React.FC\u003CLayoutProps> = ({ children, isMobile }) => {\n  return (\n    \u003Cdiv className={isMobile ? 'p-4' : 'p-8'}>\n      {children}\n    \u003C/div>\n  );\n};\n```\n\nAnd here is some CSS:\n\n```css\n.card {\n  background: white;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n  padding: 2rem;\n}\n```\n\n## Variable Fonts\n\nWith the advent of [variable fonts](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Fonts/Variable_Fonts_Guide) and better CSS support for typesetting, the web is finally catching up to print.\n\n![Abstract Shape](https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1550684848-fac1c5b4e853?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop)","src/content/blog/en/code-and-typography.md","d85f93c9dba8cfcb",{"html":298,"metadata":299},"\u003Cp>We consume content at a staggering rate. But are we actually reading? Or are we just scanning? In this essay, I explore the impact of typography on reading comprehension.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"typography-principles\">Typography Principles\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>When designing for the web, we must consider:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Hierarchy\u003C/strong>: Using size and weight to guide the eye.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Contrast\u003C/strong>: Ensuring text is legible against the background.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Cstrong>Spacing\u003C/strong>: Giving elements room to breathe.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Ch3 id=\"code-example\">Code Example\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Here is a snippet of \u003Cstrong>TypeScript\u003C/strong> code that demonstrates how we handle the layout:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cpre class=\"astro-code github-dark\" style=\"background-color:#24292e;color:#e1e4e8; overflow-x: auto;\" tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"typescript\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">interface\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#B392F0\"> LayoutProps\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#FFAB70\">  children\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#B392F0\"> React\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">.\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#B392F0\">ReactNode\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">;\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#FFAB70\">  isMobile\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#79B8FF\"> boolean\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">;\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">}\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">const\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#B392F0\"> Layout\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#B392F0\"> React\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">.\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#B392F0\">FC\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">&#x3C;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#B392F0\">LayoutProps\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">> \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">=\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\"> ({ \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#FFAB70\">children\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">, \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#FFAB70\">isMobile\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\"> }) \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">=>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">  return\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\"> (\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">    &#x3C;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">div className\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">=\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">{isMobile ? \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#9ECBFF\">'p-4'\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\"> : \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#9ECBFF\">'p-8'\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">}\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#F97583\">>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#E1E4E8\">      {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#FFAB70\">children\u